ument/Hinton_v_State_No_CR040940_2013_BL_42330_Crim_App_Feb_15_2013_Cou CR-04-0940] (Ala. Crim. App, Feb. 15, 2013); review denied, No. 1110129 (Ala., 2013)\n|subsequenthistory=\n|lawsapplied=[[Sixth Amendment to the United States Constitution|U.S. Const. amend. VI]]\n|wikisource=\n|source1=official slip opinion\n|sourceurl1=https://www.supremecourt.gov/opinions/13pdf/13-6440_m7ie.pdf\n|source2=\n|sourceurl2=\n|source3=\n|sourceurl3=\n|source4=\n|sourceurl4=\n|source5=\n|sourceurl5=\n}}\n\n==''Tolan v. Cotton''==\n{{SCOTUS per curiam\n|fullcasename=Robert R. Tolan v. Jeffrey Wayne Cotton\n|citation=572 U.S. 650\n|datedecided=May 5, 2014\n|summary=Justice Alito, joined by Justice Scalia, filed an opinion concurring in the Court's judgment.\n|priorhistory=Summary judgment granted to defendant, 854 [[Federal Supplement|F. Supp. 2d]] 444 ([[United States District Court for the Southern District of Texas|S.D. Tex.]] 2012); aff'd, 713 [[Federal Reporter|F. 3d]] 299 ([[United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit|5th Cir.]] 2013); rehearing en banc denied, 538 [[Federal Appendix|Fed. Appx.]] 374 (5th Cir. 2013)\n|subsequenthistory=\n|lawsapplied=[[Federal Rules of Civil Procedure|Fed. R. Civ. P.]] 56\n|wikisource=\n|source1=official slip opinion\n|sourceurl1=https://www.supremecourt.gov/opinions/13pdf/13-551_ihdk.pdf\n|source2=\n|sourceurl2=\n|source3=\n|sourceurl3=\n|source4=\n|sourceurl4=\n|source5=\n|sourceurl5=\n}}\n\n==''Martinez v. Illinois''==\n{{SCOTUS per curiam\n|fullcasename=Esteban Martinez v. Illinois\n|citation=572 U.S. 833\n|datedecided=May 27, 2014\n|summary=Certiorari granted. [[Supreme Court of Illinois]] reversed and remanded.\n|priorhistory=Directed verdict for defendant, [[Illinois Circuit Courts|Ill. Cir. Ct.]], [[Kane County, Illinois|Kane Cty.]], May 17, 2010; rev'd, 969 [[North Eastern Reporter|N.E. 2d]] 840 ([[Illinois Appellate Court|Ill. App. Ct.]] 2011); aff'd, 990 N.E. 2d 215 ([[Illinois Supreme Court|Ill.]] 2013)\n|subsequenthistory=\